article.headline: UNLV 80, Holy Cross 59
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Tre'Von Willis' 14 points and six rebounds led UNLV to an 80-59 victory over Holy Cross on Wednesday night. Willis, who entered the game as the Rebels' leading scorer at 16.7 points per game, connected on 7 of 11 shots. Ten players scored for the Rebels (4-0). Anthony Marshall tied Willis with 14 points, Oscar Bellfield followed with 13 and Justin Hawkins had 12. R.J. Evans led Holy Cross (0-5) with 13 points, while Mike Cavataio had nine points and a game-high 13 rebounds. The Crusaders had 24 turnovers compared to 10 for the Rebels. UNLV made 12 steals, while Holy Cross had just two. Derrick Jasper topped the Rebels with four steals, and Chace Stanback was next with three. UNLV owned a 40-28 halftime lead, and its margin never lessened.
